originalText.text:
Similar issue as others have written in their reviews - we had a coupon for a Saturday price at $30 (up to 6 hours).  Without the coupon, the sign posted outside of the garage said $42.95.  Somehow the bill came out to $60 without any explanation or breakdown and we were parked there less than 6 hours.  The coupon didn't work, and their posted sign is false.

After the show we went to get coffee and dessert hoping the line would be shorter to get our car, but even an hour after the show, it still took almost another hour for our car to be retrieved.

originalText.text: Garage tacked on additional fees that were not disclosed and have now been waiting for the car to be returned for over 45 minutes and counting. TERRIBLE service and rude staff.

originalText.text: I knew that using a parking garage was going to be expensive so that was not my issue. I know what I was signing up for in terms of cost. Especially because the location is pretty good. My issue was that when they brought my car back to me it had a FLAT tire and they said nothing. Luckily there was a lovely couple that helped put air in my tire. Meanwhile the men seem to be irritated that we were there so long because they were interacting with some other guys who were walking in and out of the garage in a very shady way. I did not feel safe and I had two children in the car. Being in such a central location I didn't realize I would have to be on such high alert. I wouldn't use this garage again. There are weird things happening whether the owners know about it or not.
